race.comment: GIGGENBACH (11) is a 4yo mare on the up having won two of her past three, running out a dominant winner at Mornington last time out when rising past a mile for the first time. Clearly relished the distance there and can go right on with it now she's hit her range. MORRISSETTE (2) is racing well. She struggled to make inroads in the Pinker Pinker Plate last time with things against but her form prior was excellent and she can bounce back. STORM AHEAD (15) presents third up having shown nice improvement last start at Geelong when boxing on well over the 1765m to finish second. Fitter again now and should handle the extra ground. SACRIFY (10) impressed with a one-length win last start at Benalla over 2100m, albeit in an easier race. Has claims.
